title: Check Your Legs Road Race
description: Road Race held on a 12.5 mile loop.  3 Categories.  Category \\\"A\\\" will be doing 3 laps.  \\\"A\\\" riders are going to be USCF Categories 1-2-3 and 4.   \\\"B\\\" riders are doing 2 laps.  \\\"B\\\" riders can be USCF Categories 3,4 and 5.   And, a field for the Women.
course: 4 right hand corners circuit.  2 climbs that are about 1/2 mile each.  Slight uphill finish.
registration: Registration is from 9:30 AM to 10:45 AM.  Day of event registration only; this is due to the unpredictable Upstate NY weather.
notes: Riders meeting will proceed the first race which will start at roughly 11:05 AM.  Subsequent fields will be started at 5 minute intervals. Food and drinks after the race. Limited bathroom facilities.  For further race information call 607-263-5605 or email petercnyc@frontiernet.net .
directions: Race start/finish is located at 3537 State Hwy. 51 in New Lisbon , NY  13415.  This location is about 4 miles North of Morris  NY or about 4 miles South of Garrattsville NY on State Hwy. 51.

Plattekill Mtn NYS CHAMPIONSHIP SERIES DS #4
Critz Farms Kermis
description: The Critz Farms Kermis will be a fun and unique timed off-road enduro-type circuit event with elements of mountain bike, cyclocross, and road racing all mixed together.  There will also be a Little 500 style team event on a small oval.  3 person teams compete over a series of 12 quick laps for bragging rights.
course: The course will be gravel roadways, dirt farm paths and a little double track all on the Critz Farms property.  It is fairly flat and fast with numerous turns.  While not technical from a mountain biking perspective, there will be 90 degree turns on gravel at speed.  The little 500 style team event will be on a short oval of approx 1/4 mi.
registration: Preregistration will be available at www.Bikereg.com.  Racers registering \\\"day of\\\" will be surcharged $5.00.
notes: Leave the road bikes home.  Some may wish to ride a \\\'cross bike, others may want a mountain bike.  While unable to predict race day conditions, a less aggressive tread will likely be the best choice.
directions:
Critz Farms is about 3.5 miles south of Cazenovia, NY on NYS Route 13 (Rippleton Road).  Cazenovia is located along NYS Route 20 approximately 20 miles southeast of Syracuse.

http://www.critzfarms.com/directions.htm

title: Sprague Brook Cyclocross
description: Modified course for this year.  Indoor changing facilities and bathrooms, showers and a course featuring complete stake and tape enclosure.  Course is mostly on grass with a couple of short road sections and short hills.  This is a fairly fast and technical course which allows space for passing for the entire distance and adheres to UCI guidelines for course design
registration:
Class	Start	Distance	Prizes

FREE KIDS RACE	Noon	Various	Prizes
